Why pinned
----------
Reproducibility (Constitution Principle V) and supply-chain hygiene
(Principle VII) require a fixed, auditable version of the ISO URL resolver.
Fetching "latest" Fido at build time would break pinning and make builds
non-deterministic, so the exact script is vendored here and invoked as a
separate, unmodified GPLv3 program (see NOTICE for the licensing boundary).

Updating
--------
1. Download Fido.ps1 for the new upstream tag.
2. Update the Pinned tag / Pinned commit fields above.
3. Re-run the local build and CI (build-image.yml) to confirm the new
   version still resolves the expected Windows 11 media.
4. Record the change in docs/change-rationale.md if behavior changes.
